2008-11-12  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>
        
        * NEWS:
        Cleaned file thanks to Eugen Dedu.

2008-11-12  Steve Frcinaux  <code@istique.net>

	* configure.ac:
	* lib/gui/gmdialog.c:
	* lib/toolbox/toolbox-gtk.c:
	* src/gui/callbacks.cpp:
	Get rid of libgnome when compiled against gtk+ >= 2.13

	libgnome was used for help display (now superseeded by gtk_show_uri) and
	for the GtkFileChooser backend through gnomevfs (now superseeded by GIO
	at the Glib level). So it is safe to drop libgnome once and for all.

2008-11-12  Steve Frcinaux  <code@istique.net>

	* src/gui/main.cpp: Get rid of GnomeProgram.

2008-11-12  Steve Frcinaux  <code@istique.net>

	* src/gui/preferences.cpp:
	Get rid of the gnome-vfs backend for the filechooser. It has been
	obsoleted by the gio support from the glib level up since Gtk+ 2.12...

2008-11-11  Steve Frcinaux  <code@istique.net>

	* lib/engine/gui/gtk-frontend/addressbook-window.cpp:
	* lib/engine/gui/gtk-frontend/book-view-gtk.cpp:
	* lib/engine/gui/gtk-frontend/call-history-view-gtk.cpp:
	* lib/engine/gui/gtk-frontend/roster-view-gtk.cpp:
	* lib/gui/gmdialog.c:
	* lib/gui/gmmenuaddon.c:
	* lib/gui/gmmenuaddon.h:
	* src/gui/accounts.cpp:
	* src/gui/main.cpp:
	* src/gui/preferences.cpp:
	* src/gui/statusicon.cpp:
	Get rid of the now-deprecated GtkSignalFunc, and use GCallback instead.

	Ekiga now compiles with
	make CFLAGS+="-DGDK_PIXBUF_DISABLE_DEPRECATED -DGDK_DISABLE_DEPRECATED
	              -DGTK_DISABLE_DEPRECATED"

2008-11-11  Steve Frcinaux  <code@istique.net>

	* lib/gui/gmlevelmeter.h:
	* lib/gui/gmlevelmeter.c:
	* src/gui/main.cpp:
	Update GmLevelMeter not to use deprecated stuff.
	- use GObject::finalize instead of GtkObject::destroy
	- use G_DEFINE_TYPE
	- Hijack GtkOrientation instead of having our own copy of it

2008-11-11  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

        * src/endpoints/sip-endpoint.cpp:
        Do not suppose the status is now offline when receiving a NOTIFY with
        an empty body.

2008-11-11  Steve Frcinaux  <code@istique.net>

	* lib/gui/gm-cell-renderer-bitext.h:
	* lib/gui/gmcellrendererexpander.c:
	* lib/gui/gmcellrendererexpander.h:
	* lib/gui/gmlevelmeter.h:
	* lib/gui/gmpowermeter.c:
	* lib/gui/gmpowermeter.h:
	Clean up GLib and GTK+ includes

	GTK+ is moving toward a model where it is only allowed to include the
	'toplevel' headers <glib.h>, <gdk/gdk.h>, <gdk-pixbuf/gdk-pixbuf.h> and
	<gtk/gtk.h> can be directly included.

	Now Ekiga compiles with
	make CFLAGS+="-DG_DISABLE_SINGLE_INCLUDES
		      -DGDK_PIXBUF_DISABLE_SINGLE_INCLUDES
		      -DGTK_DISABLE_SINGLE_INCLUDES"

2008-11-11  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

        * src/endpoints/sip-endpoint.cpp:
        Removed useless code.

