	* src/endpoints/h323-endpoint.h:
	* src/endpoints/sip-endpoint.cpp:
	* src/endpoints/sip-endpoint.h: Made it follow the new APIs.

2008-10-27  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

        * src/endpoints/manager.cpp:
        Simplified code.

2008-10-27  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

        * lib/engine/protocol/skel/call-core.cpp:
        Removed cout.

2008-10-27  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

        * src/endpoints/sip-endpoint.cpp:
        * src/endpoints/manager.cpp:
        * src/endpoints/sip-endpoint.h:
        * src/endpoints/manager.h:
        * src/endpoints/h323-endpoint.cpp:
        * src/gui/main.cpp:
        * src/gui/statusicon.cpp:
        * lib/gui/Makefile.am:
        * lib/engine/addressbook/call-history/history-book.h:
        * lib/engine/addressbook/call-history/history-book.cpp:
        * lib/engine/protocol/skel/call.h:
        * lib/engine/protocol/skel/call-core.cpp:
        * lib/engine/protocol/skel/call-core.h:
        Use gmref memory management for the Ekiga::Call objects. The principle is 
        simple, OPAL does not free OpalCall objects itself. When the Opal component 
        thinks the object should be deleted, it emits the "removed" signal on the 
        Opal::Call object, which triggers the disconnection of signals and the 
        automatic deletion when the ref count reaches zero.
        It fixes, among others, potential problems due to the OpalCall object being
        deleted too early by OPAL and still being accessed by the GUI.

2008-10-27  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

        * src/endpoints/opal-call.cpp, src/endpoints/opal-call.h:
        Do not answer or hangup calls in a separate thread, or cancelling an 
        outgoing call before it gets established won't work.

2008-10-26  Steve Frcinaux  <code@istique.net>

	* src/gui/main.cpp: Do not hardcode white background for the call
	panel, thus fixing its look with dark themes.

