2008-09-14  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* lib/gui/gmpreferences.c:
	Fixed #552241. When a device is unplugged, it is marked as insensitive
	if it was the active device, or completely removed. When a device is
	added, we check it was not already in the list. When we start Ekiga
	and the device in the prefs is not present, we display it as
	insensitive.

