	* src/Makefile.am:
	* configure.ac:
	* lib/gmmarshallers.c:
	* lib/engine/gui/gtk-frontend/Makefile.am:
	* lib/engine/components/avahi-publisher/Makefile.am:
	* lib/engine/components/avahi-publisher/avahi-publisher.h:
	* lib/engine/engine.cpp:
	* lib/engine/account/Makefile.am:
	* lib/engine/account/skel/bank-impl.h:
	* lib/engine/account/skel/bank.h:
	* lib/engine/account/skel/account.h:
	* lib/engine/account/skel/account-core.cpp:
	* lib/engine/account/skel/account-core.h:
	* lib/engine/account/skel/Makefile.am:
	* lib/engine/protocol/skel/call-core.cpp:
	* lib/engine/protocol/skel/call-core.h:
	* lib/engine/protocol/skel/call-manager.h:
	* lib/engine/presence/local-roster/local-presentity.cpp:
	* lib/engine/presence/local-roster/Makefile.am:
	* lib/engine/presence/local-roster/local-cluster.cpp:
	* lib/engine/presence/avahi/Makefile.am:
	* lib/engine/presence/skel/presence-core.h:
	* lib/engine/presence/skel/Makefile.am:
	* lib/engine/presence/skel/presence-core.cpp:
	* lib/engine/Makefile.am:
	Created an AccountCore to manage registrations. This AccountCore has
	various signals to notify from registration changes. It uses Banks of
	Accounts. It is also using AccountSubscribers which are doing the real
	job of registering an Account.
	We current support OPAL accounts registered with SIP and H323
	AccountSubscribers.
	More work to come. Initial commit.

