2008-05-25  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* src/endpoints/sip.h:
	* src/endpoints/manager.cpp:
	* src/endpoints/opal-main.cpp:
	* src/endpoints/manager.h:
	* src/endpoints/sip.cpp:
	* src/endpoints/opal-gmconf-bridge.cpp:
	A CallProtocolManager is now created with the listen port as argument
	so that it can start listening on the correct port as soon as it is
	created. Added a start () method to the GMManager so that we can
	trigger the STUNDetector only when all CallProtocolManagers are active
	and running.

2008-05-25  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* src/endpoints/sip.h:
	* src/endpoints/opal-call.cpp:
	* src/endpoints/opal-call.h:
	* src/endpoints/manager.cpp:
	* src/endpoints/manager.h:
	* src/endpoints/sip.cpp:
	* src/endpoints/opal-gmconf-bridge.cpp:
	Added back support for call forward on busy/no answer/always at the
	Opal::Call level, this feature is indeed not possible with all types
	of Calls. Added support for reject after a given delay.

