2008-01-02  Steve Frcinaux  <code@istique.net>

	* src/gui/main.cpp: fix missing #ifdef arount a GConf include.

2008-01-02  Steve Frcinaux  <code@istique.net>

	The plan is to make the core Ekiga objects unaware of the DBus
	interface exposed. The DBus component should just watch for the
	signals emitted by those objects and should not require any code
	changes in those.

	* src/components/org.ekiga.Ekiga.service.in:
	* src/components/dbus-stub.xml:
	Simplify exposed DBus interface (only one interface), and change its
	namespace to 'org.ekiga.Ekiga' (because 'net.ekiga' would be the SIP
	proxy service, not the softphone client). Remove most of the existing
	methods that were broken a few days ago.

	* src/endpoints/ekiga.h:
	* src/endpoints/ekiga.cpp:
	* src/endpoints/urlhandler.cpp:
	Make the core Ekiga objects unaware of DBus.

	* src/components/dbus.h:
	* src/components/dbus.cpp:
	Rename into EkigaDBusComponent, make it a standard GObject, adapt to
	the new interface defined above, remove most of the previously exposed
	methods (not needed anymore), remove signals, add what's needed for
	clean DBus activation and remote controlling, plug possible GError
	leaks.

	* src/gui/main.cpp:
	Use DBus activation, create the DBus component if possible and remote
	control the existing instance otherwise.

	* src/components/dbus-helper.cxx:
	* src/components/dbus-helper-stub.xml:
	Change namespage to 'org.ekiga.Helper'.

	* src/Makefile.am:
	* Makefile.am:
	* configure.ac:
	Adapt for above changes, and add --enable-dbus-service to chose
	whether or not to install the ekiga service file.

	* net.ekiga.instance.service.in:
	* net.ekiga.helper.service.in:
	removed

	* src/components/dbus_stub.xml:
	renamed into src/components/dbus-stub.xml for consistency.

2008-01-01  Steve Frcinaux  <code@istique.net>

	* Doxyfile.in:
	* configure.in:
	Generate API docs for the Ekiga Engine.

2008-01-01  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* src/endpoints/opal-call.cpp, src/endpoints/opal-call.h:
	Applied patch from Matthias Schneider to fix stupid problems
	introduced by Mr Sandras in 2007.
	Fixed packets lost percentage display.
	Got rid of the ekiga.h dependancy. This part will move in the engine
	and should not depend on ekiga at all.

