	src/gui/tools.cpp,
	src/gui/tools.h,
	src/gui/preferences.h,
	src/gui/druid.cpp,
	src/gui/druid.h,
	src/gui/callbacks.cpp,
	src/gui/accounts.cpp,
	src/gui/accounts.h,
	src/gui/callbacks.h,
	src/gui/main.cpp,
	src/gui/main.h,
	src/gui/statusicon.cpp:
	Many changes. Got rid of GnomeMeeting::Process()->GetManager(), use
	the Ekiga::ServiceCore and the CallCore instead. Addapted all objects
	to the new engine so that they do not depend on OPAL anymore. They
	depend on the engine, the engine has an OPAL implementation.

2007-12-31  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* lib/engine/framework/runtime-glib.h, lib/engine/framework/runtime.h:
	Turned the runtime into a Service. That way it can be accessed through
	the Ekiga::ServiceCore. 

2007-12-31  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* src/gui/common.h, ekiga.schemas.in.in: Added new key to contain
	audio and video codecs.

2007-12-31  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* lib/engine/addressbook/ldap/:
	Get the Runtime from the ServiceCore, not from GnomeMeeting::Process().
	Removed annoying debug.

2007-12-31  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* src/gui/conf.cpp: Moved notifiers where they should be, ie in the
	class using the related gmconf setting.

2007-12-31  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* src/components/bonobo.cpp, src/components/bonobo.h:
	Removed bonobo support. The only thing it was used for is to prevent
	to run two ekiga instances at the same time. This will be
	reimplemented using DBUS.

2007-12-31  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* lib/gui/gmcodecsbox.cpp, lib/gui/gmcodecsbox.h: 
	Adapted to the new engine codecs. The codecs box knows nothing about
	OPAL media formats. It just knows there is a key for codecs with a
	specific format.

2007-12-31  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* src/gui/preferences.cpp:
	Reordered preferences. Removed settings that the user should not
	change like the jitter buffer. The algorithm automatically calculates
	the most efficient jitter buffer value. Merged audio and video codecs
	settings. Moved bandwidth settings in the Network Settings section.

2007-12-31  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* lib/gmconf/:
	Fixed bug, gconf_value_get_list returns a list of GConfValue's, not a
	list of string. Slightly changed our API to return a list of strings.

2007-12-31  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* lib/engine/protocol/Makefile.am, lib/engine/protocol/sip/: 
	Removed all classes from protocol/sip. Call management is implemented by 
	manager.cpp and presence is implemented by sip.cpp.

2007-12-31  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* src/clients/stun.cpp: Commented out method that will be
	reimplemented later.

2007-12-31  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* src/endpoints/ekiga.cpp, src/endpoints/ekiga.h:
	General actions are not triggered anymore through
	GnomeMeeting::Process (). GUI elements use the Ekiga::ServiceCore to
	implement them: pass a reference to the Ekiga::ServiceCore to all GUI
	elements. Deprecated methods have been removed.
	The GMManager (soon to be renamed Opal::CallManager) is created
	by the engine, not by GnomeMeeting::Process() anymore.

2007-12-31  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* src/endpoints/h323.cpp, src/endpoints/h323.h:
	Purged unused functions.

2007-12-31  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* src/endpoints/sip.cpp, src/endpoints/sip.h:
	The SIPEndPoint is being used by the OPAL CallManager.
	This class also implements a PresenceFetcher.

2007-12-31  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* src/endpoints/opal-main.cpp, src/endpoints/opal-main.h: 
	Initialise the OPAL CallManager handled by the Ekiga::CallCore.

2007-12-31  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* src/endpoints/manager.h,
	src/endpoints/manager.cpp:
	Adapted the implementation so that it implements an Ekiga::CallManager 
	object using OPAL. 
	This class implements the interface defined in call-manager.h.
	This class also implements a ContactDecorator and a PresentityDecorator
	to add actions supported by the OPAL CallManager.

2007-12-31  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* src/endpoints/opal-call.h,
	src/endpoints/opal-call.cpp:
	Added the implementation of an Ekiga::Call object through OPAL. This
	class implements the interface defined in call.h.

2007-12-31  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* lib/engine/protcol/skel/call.h,
	lib/engine/protcol/skel/call-core.cpp,
	lib/engine/protcol/skel/call-core.h,
	lib/engine/protcol/skel/call-manager.h,
	lib/engine/protcol/skel/Makefile.am:
	Added the definition and implementation of objects handling calls.
	The Ekiga::CallCore manages Ekiga::CallManagers which handle
	Ekiga::Calls. It allows a Call centric approach instead of an endpoint
	centric approach.

2007-12-31  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* src/endpoint/urlhandler.cpp: 
	Simplified due to recent changes.

2007-12-31  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* devices/videodisplay.h,
	devices/videodisplay_x.cpp,
	devices/videooutput.cpp,
	devices/videodisplay_x.h,
	devices/videooutput.h,
	devices/videodisplay.cpp:
	Added a reference to the ServiceCore in order to get the Runtime from
	it and use it.

2007-12-31  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* src/devices/audio.cpp: Moved ifdef.

