	conversation.

2007-10-21  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* lib/gui/gmtextbufferaddon.c: 
	Added support for more smileys.

2007-10-21  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* src/gui/statusicon.cpp, src/gui/statusicon.h:
	Added support for the message-event signal. That way
	the blinking message icon is displayed when convenient.
	Show the chat window when the StatusIcon is clicked when
	there are unread messages, show the main window otherwise.

2007-10-21  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* src/endpoints/manager.h,
	lib/engine/gui/gtk-frontend/gtk-frontend.cpp:
	Added additional field in the new_chat signal in order
	to carry the display name of the remote peer.

2007-10-21  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* lib/engine/presence/skel/presentity.h:
	Added function to get the URI of a Presentity.

2007-10-21  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* lib/engine/gui/gtk-frontend/chat-window-page.cpp,
	lib/engine/gui/gtk-frontend/chat-window-page.h:
	Numerous changes. Display the display name and the status of 
	the remote peer people are talking to in the ChatWindowPage.
	Added documentation. Various UI enhancements in terms of focus.
	Added the possibility to add a smiley directly in the message
	composition area. Added functions to grab the focus, get/set the
	number of unread messages.

2007-10-21  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* lib/engine/gui/gtk-frontend/chat-window.cpp,
	lib/engine/gui/gtk-frontend/chat-window.h:
	Added support for new signal "message-event". Objects like the
	StatusIcon can listen to that signal in order to know if there
	are unread messages. The signal is emitted when there is a change
	in the number of unread messages, like when a message is received
	or the focus changes.

2007-10-20  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* lib/engine/framework/runtime-glib.cpp:
	Reverted broken patch.

