	src/endpoints/sip.cpp,
	src/gui/preferences.cpp,
	src/gui/druid.cpp,
	src/gui/callbacks.cpp,
	src/gui/accounts.cpp,
	src/gui/main.cpp,
	src/gui/main.h,
	src/gui/statusicon.cpp,
	src/Makefile.am,
	src/common.h,
	lib/gmcontacts/Makefile.am,
	lib/gui/gmgroupseditor.c,
	lib/gui/gmtray/Makefile.am,
	lib/gui/gmdialog.c,
	lib/gui/Makefile.am,
	lib/platform/Makefile.am,
	lib/engine/src/addressbook/Makefile.am,
	lib/engine/src/framework/Makefile.am,
	lib/engine/Makefile.am,
	lib/toolbox/Makefile.am,
	lib/druid/Makefile.am,
	lib/gmconf/gmconf-gconf.c,
	lib/gmconf/Makefile.am,
	lib/Makefile.am,
	lib/base/Makefile.am,
	autogen.sh,
	help/Makefile.am,
	Makefile.am,
	configure.in,
	configure.ac: Rather big changes to restructure
	the build system. Each component can now be compiled in
	or out independantly of the others (e.g. no EDS and storage
	of contacts in gmconf-glib for example). DISABLE_GNOME was
	not giving enough flexibility. Define _() in config.h through
	configure.ac instead of copying it from file to file. Only
	display build options if they are valid for the current
	platform.

2007-07-01  Damien Sandras  <dsandras@gnome.org>

	* configure.in, lib/engine: Added part of 
	the superb work from Julien to the repository.
	More to be added soon. Thanks !

